{"name": "async-timeout", "metadata": {"name": "async-timeout", "version": "4.0.3", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Framework :: AsyncIO", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries"], "home_page": "https://github.com/aio-libs/async-timeout", "license": "Apache 2", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Timeout context manager for asyncio programs", "upload_time": 1691685355}, "documentation": ["# async-timeout\n\n```{image} https://travis-ci.com/aio-libs/async-timeout.svg?branch=master\n:target: https://travis-ci.com/aio-libs/async-timeout\n```\n\n```{image} https://codecov.io/gh/aio-libs/async-timeout/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\n:target: https://codecov.io/gh/aio-libs/async-timeout\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/async-timeout.svg\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/async-timeout\n```\n\n```{image} https://badges.gitter.im/Join%20Chat.svg\n:alt: Chat on Gitter\n:target: https://gitter.im/aio-libs/Lobby\n```\n\nasyncio-compatible timeout context manager.\n\n## Usage example\n\nThe context manager is useful in cases when you want to apply timeout\nlogic around block of code or in cases when `asyncio.wait_for()` is\nnot suitable. Also it's much faster than `asyncio.wait_for()`\nbecause `timeout` doesn't create a new task.\n\nThe `timeout(delay, *, loop=None)` call returns a context manager\nthat cancels a block on *timeout* expiring:\n\n```\nfrom async_timeout import timeout\nasync with timeout(1.5):\n    await inner()\n```\n\n1. If `inner()` is executed faster than in `1.5` seconds nothing\n   happens.\n2. Otherwise `inner()` is cancelled internally by sending\n   `asyncio.CancelledError` into but `asyncio.TimeoutError` is\n   raised outside of context manager scope.\n\n*timeout* parameter could be `None` for skipping timeout functionality.\n\nAlternatively, `timeout_at(when)` can be used for scheduling\nat the absolute time:\n\n```\nloop = asyncio.get_event_loop()\nnow = loop.time()\n\nasync with timeout_at(now + 1.5):\n    await inner()\n```\n\nPlease note: it is not POSIX time but a time with\nundefined starting base, e.g. the time of the system power on.\n\nContext manager has `.expired` property for check if timeout happens\nexactly in context manager:\n\n```\nasync with timeout(1.5) as cm:\n    await inner()\nprint(cm.expired)\n```\n\nThe property is `True` if `inner()` execution is cancelled by\ntimeout context manager.\n\nIf `inner()` call explicitly raises `TimeoutError` `cm.expired`\nis `False`.\n\nThe scheduled deadline time is available as `.deadline` property:\n\n```\nasync with timeout(1.5) as cm:\n    cm.deadline\n```\n\nNot finished yet timeout can be rescheduled by `shift_by()`\nor `shift_to()` methods:\n\n```\nasync with timeout(1.5) as cm:\n    cm.shift(1)  # add another second on waiting\n    cm.update(loop.time() + 5)  # reschedule to now+5 seconds\n```\n\nRescheduling is forbidden if the timeout is expired or after exit from `async with`\ncode block.\n\n## Installation\n\n```\n$ pip install async-timeout\n```\n\nThe library is Python 3 only!\n\n## Authors and License\n\nThe module is written by Andrew Svetlov.\n\nIt's *Apache 2* licensed and freely available.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "async_timeout", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "async_timeout._uncancel_task", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "task", "type": {"name": "asyncio.Task", "xref": {"fqname": "asyncio.Task", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_timeout._uncancel_task", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "task", "type": {"name": "asyncio.Task", "xref": {"fqname": "asyncio.Task", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_timeout.timeout", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "delay", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Timeout", "xref": {"fqname": "Timeout", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["timeout context manager.\n\nUseful in cases when you want to apply timeout logic around block\nof code or in cases when asyncio.wait_for is not suitable. For example:\n\n```pycon\n>>> async with timeout(0.001):\n...     async with aiohttp.get('https://github.com') as r:\n...         await r.text()\n```\n\ndelay - value in seconds or None to disable timeout logic\n"]}, {"name": "async_timeout.timeout_at", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "deadline", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Timeout", "xref": {"fqname": "Timeout", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Schedule the timeout at absolute time.\n\ndeadline argument points on the time in the same clock system\nas loop.time().\n\nPlease note: it is not POSIX time but a time with\nundefined starting base, e.g. the time of the system power on.\n\n```pycon\n>>> async with timeout_at(loop.time() + 10):\n...     async with aiohttp.get('https://github.com') as r:\n...         await r.text()\n```\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "async_timeout.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "async_timeout._State", "bases": ["enum.Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "async_timeout._State.INIT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_timeout._State.ENTER", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_timeout._State.TIMEOUT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_timeout._State.EXIT", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_timeout.Timeout", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "async_timeout.Timeout.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "deadline", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "loop", "type": {"name": "asyncio.AbstractEventLoop", "xref": {"fqname": "asyncio.AbstractEventLoop", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_timeout.Timeout.__enter__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Timeout", "xref": {"fqname": "async_timeout.Timeout", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_timeout.Timeout.__exit__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exc_type", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "